    "key": "SH-126",
    "fields": {
      "summary": "Automated Task to review Hearing results",
      "attachment": [],
      "created": "2026-01-07T08:47:02.569-0700",
      "duedate": null,
      "description": {
        "type": "doc",
        "version": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "As it stands attorneys are the ones tasking paralegals to call clients for hearing related reviews. I think this task should be automated and attached to the workers compensation hearing. Even though some lawyers speak with clients after the hearing people make mistakes and sometimes forget to task paralegals to follow up on judge orders for whatever reason. This should just be automated since its a task that lawyers already task on nearly every single hearing. If we want to get fancy perhaps we can create a field for lawyers related to judge directions that would automate a task based on what the lawyer puts down so the paralegal would not have to open the hearing notes to find out the judges directions. "
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
